{
  "stem": "214.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, this Flor Levine, she was telling me that, it's a lovely family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, lovely I expected them to be, but you know, that they are-- she knows them, and if I need anything, she will advance some money for me because they were-- well, I didn't know any--",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, by this time, we did not.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and then she also promised me, she said, well, you know, pretty soon-- we don't know how soon, but it took quite a few months-- the American consulate will open in Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as soon as it opens, you will be the first-- one of the first one on the list to get a visa.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "See, the point was that you couldn't come here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You couldn't get-- I mean, you still needed affidavit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And affidavit were still from before the war because Americans didn't want, you know, immigrants.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it's only Truman in 1947 or 1948, I think, where finally that law passed through the Congress, you know, the special offer immigration of-- of-- for-- for displaced persons, for refugees, the refugees law.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we actually did arrive under-- because my cousins wrote to them, and they said they will be glad to provide an affidavit for me that I won't become a burden to the state.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was actually the main thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So and then, I mean, Beno didn't tell you how we met?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So one day, well, you know, you were always looking for lists of maybe somebody's-- I was not only looking for his name.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was looking for the names of my brothers, my sisters, and nobody remained.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one day, this was May 27-- March 27, 1948.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Beno told you.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
